TextBlock.TextLine: Brussel mr. Michel van Bellingen
C23 Juni 1682
als op 12 deser lest tot brussel was, hebbe d'een niet gehaet
van ul te sprecken, niet ul hier was, soo hebbe mijn bewijs van ƒ s00
gegeeven aen suls connecroij denchinde uet ennoodige was daer voorder
over te sprecken, want icq niet en conde ordeelen dat ul sulckx soude
weggeren, gelycq ul doet, uyt stellende nogh tot ist Jacrant van
minaechel, 26 deser is het een jaer geleden, dat ick het lest heb
gesonden, het weijnigh acoftijt, dat seg bij serdai ge y leesnde
frift mij genooesaeckt die te laeten soo versoocke ul mijn voors
bewijs te voldoenen voor de rest als ick binnen 4 weke over kome van
hove dat ul dat sal oock af macken ter wijlen dat in alle vervalle
ende occatie ul geirne sal diene & blijve
London i ab: Vivian
daveing non of yd to answer, do onely send you the invoyce of the packett
N.8 omitted in mine of the 21 crutt, I do much long to understand what
goods am a board smiss, & in what forwardness, our bustijnes an Inthe north
for Ifinde that time stands not still, & wee could sell unthn or 3 weekes
againe for ½ july our sale beguis. the acctt. of sales you dare with yu
for I do not finde them gere, butt in case you should have lost them
shall send you others, the laces you carnied with you are noted oithe
packett n. 6, as I supose beeng n. 139: 140:141 & 142 so please to epanin
itt, if itt be not so, in the meane while I finde that the ale conde
not heep bill vere, so wee shall bave non, bett the cheese I supose
maij keep: remember mee to all frineds
london m: Henry Maynaid
mij last to you was on the 20t curitt with a bill of £150- on Juhn lambe which
I hope you dave recd. behore this, as also the formars. haveing now before
mee yds of the g. curtt., I have answered you the needfull about Peeters buste s
which soones I could not do, for I was att Brussels, yett thee was butt one
post day omitted, & as f told you £155„3:2 is the ballance flemish, which
in case m. slanghter or you draw on mee att 2ul, shall be duly pare daving
a discharge of m. slaughter as desired. I take notue what you bid for ie
pack whites, pray dispatch 5 of oach sort, as soone as you can, meet the
to yd minde, & ther itt may be a monsh sence thay will be yett cheaper
to have some mone you please also not to omitt alowert sort, for I
suppose I shall want as much againe pack wsites yearly, as ever I did
I have in all butt 6 by mee. I could wish the at. silver mancy ware
here, & that the maker was quicker att itt, because before sber I must
have no less then 10 p with mee, I hope de will abate dis prijses is
well as other dor yett. I would not have you stand upon a small
masser soengage n to do well, & to makee them the bester, & ther when
wee an in with dim, I supose you can make a baagen, I wonder the ssamet
should terry so longh, I could with thee werr 2 or 3 of y for a ryall, becausse
sence I am more desired for y & am of opinion to sill good quantities a yeare
las for the salen of april the cottens must be 1½ snall 6½, for the other
is noted the 21 of marck, te bayes com to ƒ 442- so that will be recties
on therept, I save given you creditt for my ½ in the bale aboard Bater
& made you debtor for the £150- drawne on mee, & first you please to
provide 3 or 4 mochs ven, 2 of abont 5 ƒ one of 5:6, & one of a baut ƒ7-
ayd, which you may putt amonghst the spanish cloathes, is then no
nhew mode yett, for itt geems ett must be yett draps, & browne with ins
London mr. Cucy Kinghtley
C 24 Juni 1682
my last to you was on the 17t cutt sence non from you m. Coller is now cst
Lille, wee have settled & adiusted all our corcernes, which I sippose hin
some in londen die not know, when be desired you to draw on mee, for dis
fackers acctt. otherwise je would not have don itt, yett have accepted the biel
for you, & place itt to my acctt, m. Collies wrot mee he would rembourse
you the valeuw, so make no difference in acctt
Mechelen nm Cornelis van Aken de onge
desen tot covert van de facture van 4 goet aen ul vercoght, met den st.dagh soo is gistren
geen schip aen de laedinge geweest, sal dan eerst morgen connen gelaeden woorden
wil hopen datul daer door geen preiud sal lijden, volgens ul ad. sal de
baggeijntiens juff wigans duff Peeters bijul sejnden, ul can aen hin yder
de '4 geeven van 't gene ul sal gelegen comen voor mij te bet, nomende un
quitantie sal ul valideere
Mechelen Juff. Anna inigans
m. Comelis van Aken de Jonge heeft mij geseyt als dat hij voor mij aen ul eenigh
gelt sal tellen, soo can ul met gelegentheyt dat ontf, geloove ontrentƒ 250
sijn sal & geeven quitantie, &mij laeten weeten wat ontf sult heb ben
Mechelen Juff. Barvara Peeters
wille niet twijffelen oft ul heeft mijnen van 22 deser ontf met detste cant
mr. van aken den jonge laken vercoopen aen d'ijsere been sal aenule ƒ 200
oft ƒ 250- gelt tellen, ul can desen mijnen brief dem laeten sien, & aen hem
quitantie geeven voor soo veel als het hem sal geleegen comen aen ul te
tellen, & stelt het selve op mijn recq & adviseert het gepasseerden
